scheduled tournaments plan:

phase 1a done:
- added schema compatibility fields/enums
- added migration for scheduled tournament fields
- added creationMode / registrationMode / previewBracketData / registrationStatus types
- kept old confirmed/declined flow working for quick tournaments

agreed product behavior:
- private scheduled tournaments = invite only
- public scheduled tournaments = open signup OR approval required
- invites always exist
- participants in v1 = accounts + teams
- bracket generates on start
- organizer sees/tweaks preview before start
- start mode = manual first, auto-start later

recommended mvp scope:
- separate scheduled create page + form
- create scheduled tournament in registration state
- registration modes: invite_only / open / approval
- register/request/invite endpoints
- organizer approve/decline entrants
- organizer preview bracket
- manual start endpoint to generate final bracket and set active

schema added:
- tournament.creation_mode = quick | scheduled
- tournament.registration_mode = invite_only | open | approval
- tournament.auto_start
- tournament.registration_closes_at
- tournament.preview_bracket_data
- tournament.started_at
- tournament_participant.registration_status = invited | pending | approved | declined | withdrawn

next phase (1b):
- POST /tournaments/scheduled
- POST /tournaments/:id/register
- DELETE /tournaments/:id/register
- PATCH /tournaments/:id/respond-invite
- PATCH /tournaments/:id/participants/:seed/approve
- PATCH /tournaments/:id/participants/:seed/decline
- POST /tournaments/:id/preview-bracket
- POST /tournaments/:id/start

frontend after backend:
- enable scheduled card on tournaments/create
- add app/tournaments/create/scheduled/page.tsx
- add ScheduledTournamentForm
- update tournament view page with registration / approval / preview / start UI

important:
- quick and scheduled should stay separate flows
- do not overload quick tournament form
- manual start first, true auto-start later with worker/scheduler